abstract: HILTON HEAD ISLAND, S.C., May 4 Hollis Stacy dropped a 6-foot putt for a birdie on the first playoff hole today and beat Amy Alcott for the $15,000 first prize in the fifth $100,000 Women's International golf tournament.
headline_main: Miss Stacy Triumphs in Golf Playoff
headline_print_headline: Miss Stacy Triumphs in Golf Playoff
byline_original: By Gordon S. White Jr. Special To the New York Times

abstract: HILTON HEAD, S.C., May 3--Amy Alcott, Sally Little and Hollis Stacy, who have 22 victories among them on the Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour, were tied for the lead at 209, seven under par, today after three rounds of the $100,000 Women's International tournament.
